definition: abbr. for Xinjiang 新疆[Xin1 jiang1] or Singapore 新加坡[Xin1 jia1 po1]/surname Xin

sentences.english: Include the latest edition of the local paper, magazines that might be of interest or your local “What’s Up?
sentences.chinese: 包括最新版的当地报纸，杂志。

sentences.english: New version of iciba gave her new face to everybody in the particular area.
sentences.chinese: 新版爱词霸在这块特有的领地里给大家一幅新面孔。

sentences.english: It is recommended that you install the latest version to avoid encountering problems that have already been fixed.
sentences.chinese: 推荐您安装最新版，以避免遇到已经被修复的问题。

sentences.english: The original lucky star big market, packed with the latest version of the software trade.
sentences.chinese: 原版的大福星行情系统，打包了最新版的交易软件。

sentences.english: Oral English will be a new, welcome you to write articles or book reports.
sentences.chinese: 英语墙报将出新版，欢迎大家写文章或读书报告。

sentences.english: The greater openness of the new version may be more appealing to the young.
sentences.chinese: 新版红楼的更大尺度的开放或许能吸引更多年轻观众。

sentences.english: The new $100s look busier than the paper bills.
sentences.chinese: 新版的100加元钞票比原来的纸币上图像更多一点。

sentences.english: The company sent me the new version of the migration program and it worked.
sentences.chinese: 苹果公司给我送来了新版的转移程序，这次成功了。

sentences.english: Sheng writes in an afterword to a new edition of her novel, published this year.
sentences.chinese: 盛可以在今年新版的后记中写到。

sentences.english: The new textbook College English is humanism-based.
sentences.chinese: 新版《大学英语》是一种以人为本的教材。

sentences.english: This new edition of this old book is an excellent one.
sentences.chinese: 这本旧书的新版做得非常好。

sentences.english: A new edition of each volume is published at intervals of about 15 months.
sentences.chinese: 每一卷灯标雾号表的新版大约15个月出版一次。

sentences.english: Documentation updated, new "update. exe" file which is no longer detected by Avira as trojan.
sentences.chinese: 文件更新，新版已不再被杀软视为木马程序。

sentences.english: The new leads lack the star quality of the old version.
sentences.chinese: 比起老版的演员，新版的看上去没什么明星相。

sentences.english: HTML5 is the latest iteration of this lingua franca.
sentences.chinese: HTML5是这门通用语言的最新版。

sentences.english: Today's economy offers evidence for the next edition of their book.
sentences.chinese: 如今的经济状况可以为他们的新版著作提供例证。

definition: to revise the current edition/revised edition
to reproduce photographically/to duplicate/to adapt (as a movie)/to remake (a movie)/adaptation/reproduction/remake
to replace the old with new/to renew/to renovate/to upgrade/to update/to regenerate
government/official (approved or issued by an authority)
to abridge (a text)/to edit out (of a movie)/to cut back (a budget, a curriculum)
